"Some day, all I'm going to have is my opinions and my loud mouth."  Don't be so hard on yourself, Amber...you'll have your cellmates, and outdoor recreation every day, communal meals, and I'm certain you'll have plenty of prison pen-pals!  You'll have *lots* of time to catch up on your reading, and plenty of time to paint (but don't throw the solvent cans...the prison guards don't like that)!
     
      NNnnno.....the girl from Austin, Texas, *thinks* she's smart.  *Being* smart, is when you take a great deal of time, and do extensive research, in order to attempt to frame someone for domestic abuse.  You don't want to just throw it together with some friends over a couple of dozen bottles of wine.  *In fact* , *being smart* would be *not* attempting to manipulate a marriage to achieve money and fame, because you will become exposed as the criminal that you are...and then you will go to jail! 
     
      Amber Heard, *atheist stripper* , into sex (with men who can get her the things that she wants...or with the women that she *is actually attracted to* ), drugs ("All I was poppin' was Xanax, Adderall, Ecstasy and hallucinogens!"), and money ($50,000 per month support, the black Range Rover [Mr. Depp to cover all costs], three of the Eastern Columbia Building Penthouse Apartments worth $13,000,000--Mr. Depp to cover costs, fees and utilities, $150,000 lawyers fees, $25,000 forensic accounting fees, and an undisclosed divorce settlement!)
     
     So...Ms. Heard is "in it" for "the challenge of older, annoying men, who piss her off."  I suppose that it's easier to physically assault someone, slander them, defame them, and attempt to extort money from them if they are simply "a challenge", and not someone that she would be capable of loving... *IF* she *IS* capable of loving anyone other than *HERSELF!*
    
      "She knows her limits."  Ha. Ha. Ha. Ha. Ha!  She *thinks* she knows her limits.  Her downfall will be...*THINKING* that she is *SO* much *smarter* than she *IS!*  When Mr. Depp showed up to the apartment with witnesses, and the Police insisted upon doing an investigation...Amber Heard should have cut her losses and ran.  Made her divorce as amiable as possible.  Kept everything out of the press.  Mr. Depp would have given her a generous settlement (likely anything she had asked for).  He would still be her friend, and would be pulling Hollywood strings to get her good roles.  She would find herself invited to important social gatherings...and remained part of the fashionable crowd...instead, her name is a pariah, her career is over, and she's heading for jail.  Sadly, she worked very hard to accomplish this exact outcome.  She dropped out of school at fifteen, and decided that she had *other* attributes that she could use to make money.  She may *hold* intelligent books, but she wasn't looking to catch an intellectual,  she was looking to catch a bank account.  Johnny Depp bought her the library of classic books, and Kate James arranged them on the shelves...all for looks.
